    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "The utility method `replaceListChild` replace the child of a given lists column with a new child. This is not a copy operation but instead just creating a new column view. As such, the new child column is expected to outlive the newly created lists column. Otherwise, this will cause use-after-free bug when the new child is closed before the new lists column is accessed. For example:\r\n```\r\nval newChild = getNewChild();\r\nval newListsColumn = withResource(newChild) { inputLists.replaceListChild(_) }\r\n\r\n// Use newListsColumn here. However, this may cause data corruption since newChild has been closed.\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe should better document the `replaceListChild` method or better implement it to avoid such bug.",
